---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { routes } from '../../i18n/utils';

const lang = 'en';
const r = routes[lang];
const updated = 'July 7, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="Soulmarket's privacy policy: what data we collect through the contact form, why we collect it and how to exercise your rights."
  lang={lang}
>
  <header class="hero-columns relative overflow-hidden pt-28 md:pt-36 pb-8 md:pb-12">
    <div class="container-lg relative">
      <h1 class="reveal fadeInUp giant-heading text-ink mb-0">
        <em class="block">privacy</em>
        <span class="block">policy</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal fadeInUp text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted mt-6" style="--reveal-delay:0.1s">
        Last updated: {updated}
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="container-sm pb-20 md:pb-28 prose-content">
    <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
    <p>
      The controller of the personal data collected on soulmarket.com is
      <strong>Soulmarket</strong> <!-- TODO: add legal name, tax ID and postal address before launch -->
      ("Soulmarket"). You can reach us at
      <a href="mailto:hola@soulmarket.com">hola@soulmarket.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What data we collect and why</h2>
    <p>
      Through the <a href={r.contact}>contact form</a> we collect your name, email address and the
      content of your message, for the sole purpose of replying to your enquiry and, if you request
      it, preparing a commercial proposal.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not use this data to send unsolicited advertising, nor do we add it to mailing lists
      without your express consent.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      The legal basis for processing is your <strong>consent</strong>, given by ticking the
      acceptance checkbox before submitting the form (art. 6.1.a GDPR), and our legitimate interest
      in replying to commercial enquiries (art. 6.1.f GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>4. Where your data is stored</h2>
    <p>
      Data is stored in our own management system, hosted on a server contracted with OVH within
      the European Union. No international transfers outside the European Economic Area take place.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
    <p>
      We do not share your data with third parties except where legally required. We do not use
      external form platforms: messages go directly to our systems.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your data for the duration of the commercial relationship or, for enquiries that do
      not lead to a project, for a maximum of two years after the last contact, after which it is
      deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection, restriction of
      processing and portability at any time by writing to
      <a href="mailto:hola@soulmarket.com">hola@soulmarket.com</a>. You also have the right to file
      a complaint with the <a href="https://www.aepd.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD)</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      This website does not use tracking or advertising cookies. The only cookies or local storage
      that may exist are those strictly necessary for the site to work. If we add analytics in the
      future, this policy will be updated and consent requested where required.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      Any relevant change to this policy will be published on this page with its update date.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
